{"TopicId":187338,"ForumId":109,"TopicTitle":"KSP2 Hype Train Thread","CreatedByName":"Whirligig Girl","CreatedById":36077,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-19T20:46:45Z","PageNum":27,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Admiral Fluffy","CreatedById":210816,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-23T21:29:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224081269\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206443\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221642971837\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022212979\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022gussi111\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n24 minutes ago, gussi111 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI hope this silence means that they are working on a gameplay trailer or something equally big.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe gameplay itself!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheOrbitalMechanic","CreatedById":216179,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-23T22:30:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224081136\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206443\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221642956716\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022213541\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022t_v\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, t_v said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nexcited to (accidentally)(intentionally) crash into a big base with torch drive fuel.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaster Plan:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1. \u0022Gift\u0022 rival player a metallic hydrogen factory for their colony\u003Cbr\u003E\n2. Crash into it\u003Cbr\u003E\n3. Profit\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"gussi111","CreatedById":212979,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-24T17:11:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224081530\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206443\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221643038455\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022137773\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022siklidkid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, siklidkid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDay 10\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nsiklidkid I\u0027m melting your catto in a glass.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDay 10 woo hooo! Only 341 days left in 2022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"BekfastDerp13","CreatedById":214450,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-24T17:39:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have lost track of my waiting days, but I want to make a giant colony on Rask or Rusk, then throw it into lava. Like that scene from Revenge of the Sith, but everything falls in.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mmamh2008","CreatedById":216764,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-24T17:51:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOK , let\u0027s analyze some parts with the new WIP UI\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022r/KerbalSpaceProgram - The new KSP 2 UI looks much better\u0022 data-ratio=\u002285.70\u0022 style=\u0022max-height:700px;\u0022 width=\u0022790\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.redd.it/pc95zvpldk151.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe UI looks great , That\u0027s KerbalX I think.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022A new look at KSP 2 launch trailer - KSP 2 Discussion - Kerbal Space Program  Forums\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 style=\u0022width:585px;height:329.063px;margin:0px;\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/TcGuaD0.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022https://cdn.akamai.steamstatic.com/steam/apps/954850/extras/KSP2_GIF_3.gif?t=1605113138\u0022 data-ratio=\u002233.33\u0022 width=\u0022600\u0022 src=\u0022https://cdn.akamai.steamstatic.com/steam/apps/954850/extras/KSP2_GIF_3.gif?t=1605113138\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLook carefully , Engines seemed to turn off separately , launch failures ? Now the Abort system is a need . The smoke looks like it\u0027s WIP though\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022KSP2 Flight UI from Developer Story Trailer - Page 2 - KSP 2 Discussion - Kerbal  Space Program Forums\u0022 data-ratio=\u002278.75\u0022 style=\u0022width:585px;height:329.063px;margin:0px;\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/QtlQMfR.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnother UI prototype\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022An HD look at the KSP 2 VAB : Kerbal Space Program, Video Game, Gaming :  r/KerbalSpaceProgram\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 style=\u0022width:585px;height:329.063px;margin:0px;\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://preview.redd.it/81o7b9od0b851.jpg?auto=webp\u0026amp;s=8b9fc66d680be6629e69a74709798e648ff670c2\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk , so there are castor decouplers and sperate fuel tanks that appear as one ? also the name of this rocket is kerbal Gryphon orbiter MK 16 , So there are 15 MK rockets before that , interesting\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"daninplainsight","CreatedById":214296,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-24T18:17:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m really curious to see what indicators they add while doing docking maneuvers, or if they add parallel/anti-parallel attitude modes. We definitely need more granular readouts in stock as to relative orientation and position to a targeted docking port.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Catto","CreatedById":137773,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-24T18:39:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224081592\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206443\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221643046663\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022216764\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mmamh2008\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n45 minutes ago, mmamh2008 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOK , let\u0027s analyze some parts with the new WIP UI\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.redd.it/pc95zvpldk151.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022r/KerbalSpaceProgram - The new KSP 2 UI looks much better\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002285.70\u0022 style=\u0022max-height:700px;\u0022 width=\u0022790\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.redd.it/pc95zvpldk151.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe UI looks great , That\u0027s KerbalX I think.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHOLD ON, How did they get to orbit without even decoupling their boosters? The KSP Devteam has been eXposed!!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mmamh2008","CreatedById":216764,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-24T18:41:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224081612\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206443\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221643049540\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022137773\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022siklidkid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, siklidkid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHOLD ON, How did they get to orbit without even decoupling their boosters? The KSP Devteam has been eXposed!!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s a test , not a real launch LOL\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"shdwlrd","CreatedById":113880,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-24T19:58:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224081592\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206443\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221643046663\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022216764\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mmamh2008\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, mmamh2008 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/TcGuaD0.jpg\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022A new look at KSP 2 launch trailer - KSP 2 Discussion - Kerbal Space Program  Forums\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 style=\u0022width:585px;height:329.063px;margin:0px;\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/TcGuaD0.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, that is one single ship. You can see it departing in the trailer and accelerating away from Jool. The forum probably ate the tread, but the scales of parts will be expanding in KSP2. There will have to be parts larger that the 5m seen in KSP1 to create that monster craft and station but keep the part count to a reasonable amount.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mmamh2008","CreatedById":216764,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-24T20:10:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224081658\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206443\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221643054286\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022113880\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022shdwlrd\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, shdwlrd said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, that is one single ship. You can see it departing in the trailer and accelerating away from Jool. The forum probably ate the tread, but the scales of parts will be expanding in KSP2. There will have to be parts larger that the 5m seen in KSP1 to create that monster craft and station but keep the part count to a reasonable amount.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know , that was as Image I found on google so I put in here if there\u0027s something somebody doesn\u0027t know\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n5m parts , hmm interesting ( Saturn V hops in mind )\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know that the part list goes over 1000 parts\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-01-24T20:12:46Z\u0022 title=\u002201/24/2022 08:12  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 24, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by mmamh2008\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"shdwlrd","CreatedById":113880,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-24T20:49:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224081669\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206443\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221643055011\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022216764\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mmamh2008\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 minutes ago, mmamh2008 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know , that was as Image I found on google so I put in here if there\u0027s something somebody doesn\u0027t know\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n5m parts , hmm interesting ( Saturn V hops in mind )\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know that the part list goes over 1000 parts\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk, fair enough.\u00A0\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNobody outside of Intercept knows how many parts there will be. There could be a few hundred if some form of procedural sizing and fuel switching is used. (Mostly utility parts instead of tanks, structural, and wing parts.) Or several hundred if they stick with the KSP1 style of organizing the parts. (I hope not.) But they did show a procedural wings demo, that gives me hope that there will be some expansion of the procedural options for the other commonly used parts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MechBFP","CreatedById":184845,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-24T21:29:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224081612\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206443\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221643049540\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022137773\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022siklidkid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, siklidkid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHOLD ON, How did they get to orbit without even decoupling their boosters? The KSP Devteam has been eXposed!!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat is just their Eve lander, so perfectly normal.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-24T21:43:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow you can hype KSP2 by posting every day until it comes out, because these threads have been merged.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"t_v","CreatedById":213541,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-24T22:25:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nday 6 (for me)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nexcited to fly my first baristochrone trajectory\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Deddly","CreatedById":62955,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-25T06:54:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust a little reminder, please keep \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/guidelines/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Eguideline 2.2m\u003C/a\u003E in mind while posting and avoid making posts that have no content. Some of those comments have been removed.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mmamh2008","CreatedById":216764,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-25T11:30:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224081713\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221643060595\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002227914\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vanamonde\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, Vanamonde said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow you can hype KSP2 by posting every day until it comes out, because these threads have been merged.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk , we now have a single thread , RIP old thread\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224081695\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221643057361\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022113880\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022shdwlrd\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 hours ago, shdwlrd said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk, fair enough.\u00A0\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNobody outside of Intercept knows how many parts there will be. There could be a few hundred if some form of procedural sizing and fuel switching is used. (Mostly utility parts instead of tanks, structural, and wing parts.) Or several hundred if they stick with the KSP1 style of organizing the parts. (I hope not.) But they did show a procedural wings demo, that gives me hope that there will be some expansion of the procedural options for the other commonly used parts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe procedural idea is better , It\u0027ll save a lot of space ... and loading time\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224081695\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221643057361\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022113880\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022shdwlrd\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 hours ago, shdwlrd said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthat gives me hope that there will be some expansion of the procedural options for the other commonly used parts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWait a second . Wha .... You\u0027re right ! Look a this metallic bar on the orange tank \u003Cspan\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022An HD look at the KSP 2 VAB : Kerbal Space Program, Video Game, Gaming :  r/KerbalSpaceProgram\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 style=\u0022width:585px;height:329.063px;margin:0px;\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://preview.redd.it/81o7b9od0b851.jpg?auto=webp\u0026amp;s=8b9fc66d680be6629e69a74709798e648ff670c2\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt looks that it\u0027s procedural but the metallic bar also looks like struts\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"gussi111","CreatedById":212979,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-25T11:56:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat new capsule looks dope! So far we have only seen how colonies look like when they are massive and advanced, I want to see how the first colonies will look like that can only house maybe 3-4 Kerbals, what parts will you need to bring? will you be able to for example connect power producing parts with habitation parts of the colony with cables? That would make working with different parts on the surface much easier because you wouldn\u0027t have to dock every part to another with a docking port or a claw.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-01-25T12:01:46Z\u0022 title=\u002201/25/2022 12:01  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 25, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by gussi111\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Laxez","CreatedById":216956,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-25T12:19:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the first KSP there were not many options if I wanted big tanks with only liquid oxygen, it would be interesting if they made all tanks dynamic, so that you can choose diameter, height and type of fuel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nObviously the orion engine will have different tanks due to the different type of fuel that is solid, and also other engines that will need specific types of fuel that is not liquid will have a separate tank type.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mmamh2008","CreatedById":216764,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-25T12:45:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224081895\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221643111778\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022212979\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022gussi111\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n48 minutes ago, gussi111 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat new capsule looks dope! So far we have only seen how colonies look like when they are massive and advanced, I want to see how the first colonies will look like that can only house maybe 3-4 Kerbals, what parts will you need to bring? will you be able to for example connect power producing parts with habitation parts of the colony with cables? That would make working with different parts on the surface much easier because you wouldn\u0027t have to dock every part to another with a docking port or a claw.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d like to replicate the martian but in more kerbal way , the cables are very important , I was thinking of that some hours ago and yeah , We could have some nasa-like base parts at first for housing the first crewed missions and then the R\u0026amp;D makes new technologies send them .... etc\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-01-25T12:45:59Z\u0022 title=\u002201/25/2022 12:45  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 25, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by mmamh2008\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Admiral Fluffy","CreatedById":210816,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-25T15:50:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224081908\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221643114742\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022216764\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mmamh2008\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, mmamh2008 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d like to replicate the martian but in more kerbal way\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMoar boosters?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Catto","CreatedById":137773,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-25T16:30:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwait this isn\u0027t my thread\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOHH It is they got merged\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:o\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/ZNGIcon2.png\u0022 title=\u0022:o\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn that case: Day 11\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-01-25T16:30:58Z\u0022 title=\u002201/25/2022 04:30  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 25, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by siklidkid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"t_v","CreatedById":213541,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-25T16:38:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nday 6\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nexcited to fall down a surprise ravine in a rover\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mmamh2008","CreatedById":216764,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-25T17:41:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224082011\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221643128236\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022137773\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022siklidkid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, siklidkid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwait this isn\u0027t my thread\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOHH It is they got merged\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:o\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/ZNGIcon2.png\u0022 title=\u0022:o\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn that case: Day 11\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYour thread is dead now , press F to say RIP\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224081979\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221643125830\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210816\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Admiral Fluffy\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Admiral Fluffy said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMoar boosters?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nnope , kerpstein drive\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"gussi111","CreatedById":212979,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-25T18:44:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo yeah I think having fuel lines and cables to connect a bunch of different parts on the ground is a great idea, imagine having to somehow dock all parts of a huge colony together to have power for example. With this you can have power generating parts like reactors and windmills and mining sites far away from the habitation and refinery part of the colony (for esthetic or other purposes) while still supplying power and ore for the colony to function and produce fuel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat do others think? \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-01-25T20:38:45Z\u0022 title=\u002201/25/2022 08:38  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 25, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by gussi111\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mmamh2008","CreatedById":216764,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-25T19:49:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224082083\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221643136299\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022212979\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022gussi111\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n57 minutes ago, gussi111 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo yeah I think having fuel lines and cables to connect a bunch of different parts on the ground is a great idea, imagine having to somehow dock all parts of a huge colony together to have power for example. With this you can have power generating parts like reactors and windmills and mining sites far away from the habitation part of the colony (for esthetic or other purposes) while still supplying power and ore for the colony to function and produce fuel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat do others think? \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nso yeah , the show and tell videos of fuel makers and nuclear power generators tell me that they need to be far enough and in this picture you se that nothing is docked so cables should be there\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022r/KerbalSpaceProgram - This image has less haze and has a great sunset light reflection\u0022 data-ratio=\u002269.25\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://preview.redd.it/ubettd9agyx71.png?width=1500\u0026amp;format=png\u0026amp;auto=webp\u0026amp;s=118e7da96af2298d228ba037a3665736397e07d8\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is the image\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd this is my best reddit post which has some ksp 2 things included \u003Cspan\u003E: \u003C/span\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.reddit.com/r/KerbalSpaceProgram/comments/qny2pq/what_i_have_noticed_in_ksp_2_and_seemed_good_to/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.reddit.com/r/KerbalSpaceProgram/comments/qny2pq/what_i_have_noticed_in_ksp_2_and_seemed_good_to/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}